{"id":"3900669976","type":"page","ari":"ari:cloud:confluence:4e3a1a04-13f1-4674-95f6-44812aec1da3:page/3900669976","base64EncodedAri":"YXJpOmNsb3VkOmNvbmZsdWVuY2U6NGUzYTFhMDQtMTNmMS00Njc0LTk1ZjYtNDQ4MTJhZWMxZGEzOmNvbnRlbnQvMzkwMDY2OTk3Ng==","status":"current","title":"Picasso/Angus: Parámetros opcionales de respuesta","version":{"by":{"type":"known","accountId":"712020:bd6be9b3-2ff0-412b-8fb1-57e9e188f6cf","accountType":"atlassian","email":"","publicName":"Gastón Gabadian","profilePicture":{"path":"/wiki/aa-avatar/712020:bd6be9b3-2ff0-412b-8fb1-57e9e188f6cf","width":48,"height":48,"isDefault":false},"displayName":"Gastón Gabadian","isExternalCollaborator":false,"isGuest":false,"locale":"en_US","accountStatus":"active","_expandable":{"operations":"","personalSpace":""},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/user?accountId=712020:bd6be9b3-2ff0-412b-8fb1-57e9e188f6cf"}},"when":"2025-04-17T18:28:34.043Z","friendlyWhen":"Apr 17, 2025","message":"","number":4,"minorEdit":false,"ncsStepVersion":"3041","ncsStepVersionSource":"ncs-ack","confRev":"confluence$content$3900669976.99","contentTypeModified":false,"_expandable":{"collaborators":"","content":"/rest/api/content/3900669976"},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/3900669976/version/4"}},"ancestors":[{"id":"2178416778","type":"page","ari":"ari:cloud:confluence:4e3a1a04-13f1-4674-95f6-44812aec1da3:page/2178416778","base64EncodedAri":"YXJpOmNsb3VkOmNvbmZsdWVuY2U6NGUzYTFhMDQtMTNmMS00Njc0LTk1ZjYtNDQ4MTJhZWMxZGEzOmNvbnRlbnQvMjE3ODQxNjc3OA==","status":"current","title":"Bancard","macroRenderedOutput":{},"extensions":{"position":878},"_expandable":{"container":"/rest/api/space/BAN","metadata":"","restrictions":"/rest/api/content/2178416778/restriction/byOperation","history":"/rest/api/content/2178416778/history","body":"","version":"","descendants":"/rest/api/content/2178416778/descendant","space":"/rest/api/space/BAN","childTypes":"","schedulePublishInfo":"","operations":"","schedulePublishDate":"","children":"/rest/api/content/2178416778/child","ancestors":"","draftVersion":""},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/2178416778","tinyui":"/x/igDYgQ","editui":"/pages/resumedraft.action?draftId=2178416778","webui":"/spaces/BAN/overview","edituiv2":"/spaces/BAN/pages/edit-v2/2178416778"}},{"id":"2259944189","type":"page","ari":"ari:cloud:confluence:4e3a1a04-13f1-4674-95f6-44812aec1da3:page/2259944189","base64EncodedAri":"YXJpOmNsb3VkOmNvbmZsdWVuY2U6NGUzYTFhMDQtMTNmMS00Njc0LTk1ZjYtNDQ4MTJhZWMxZGEzOmNvbnRlbnQvMjI1OTk0NDE4OQ==","status":"current","title":"Documentación Técnica","macroRenderedOutput":{},"extensions":{"position":44304616},"_expandable":{"container":"/rest/api/space/BAN","metadata":"","restrictions":"/rest/api/content/2259944189/restriction/byOperation","history":"/rest/api/content/2259944189/history","body":"","version":"","descendants":"/rest/api/content/2259944189/descendant","space":"/rest/api/space/BAN","childTypes":"","schedulePublishInfo":"","operations":"","schedulePublishDate":"","children":"/rest/api/content/2259944189/child","ancestors":"","draftVersion":""},"_links":{"self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/2259944189","tinyui":"/x/-QK0hg","editui":"/pages/resumedraft.action?draftId=2259944189","webui":"/spaces/BAN/pages/2259944189/Documentaci+n+T+cnica","edituiv2":"/spaces/BAN/pages/edit-v2/2259944189"}}],"macroRenderedOutput":{},"body":{"storage":{"value":"<p>Esta feature posibilita incluir ciertos atributos en la respuesta de las operaciones del servicio seg&uacute;n alg&uacute;n criterio. Por ejemplo, un criterio podr&iacute;a ser si el cliente solicit&oacute; el par&aacute;metro opcional.</p><p>Los par&aacute;metros opcionales deben ser identificados en el archivo <code>operations.yml</code> o  <code>representations.yml</code> (seg&uacute;n en donde se posicione en la estructura de la respuesta) con el atributo <code>optional: true</code> . </p><p>Por default:</p><ul><li><p>ning&uacute;n atributo es opcional. El framework arma el JSON de respuesta con todos los atributos definidos en los archivos <code>operations.yml</code> y <code>representations.yml</code>. Los atributos opcionales deben ser expl&iacute;citamente declarados como tal.</p></li><li><p>los atributos definidos como opcionales no son devueltos al cliente en el JSON de respuesta.</p></li></ul><h1>Par&aacute;metros opcionales: introducci&oacute;n</h1><p>Definimos una operaci&oacute;n sin par&aacute;metros de entrada que devuelve un body con un elemento <code>test_optional_attrs</code> de tipo <code>optional_attrs_representation</code></p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"5a8fc34b-6577-4283-9210-e42a3acd0ef3\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# operations.yml\n\ntest_optional_attrs:\n  name: probar atrs opcionales\n  description: Probar atrs opcionales\n  path: /test_optional_attrs\n  method: post\n\n  response:\n    - element: test_optional_attrs\n      description: Probar atrs opcionales\n      required: false\n      type: optional_attrs_representation]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>Definimos la representation <code>optional_attrs_represetnation</code> con dos atributos. Uno convencional y otro opcional.</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"9cbb0e67-15ae-455e-ad16-f52c346d05ee\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# representations.yml\n\noptional_attrs_representation:\n  - field: a\n    description: A\n    type: string\n    required: true\n  - field: b\n    description: B\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    optional: true # Atributo opcional]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>En la implementaci&oacute;n de la operaci&oacute;n, devolvemos un objeto que se adec&uacute;a a la estructura de la response de la operation.</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"33a34784-6462-4c75-b38a-c8c1fb06b6fb\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb\n\nhandle_operation(:test_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: {\n      a: :a,\n      b: :b\n    }\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>Resultado:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"949\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-204709.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-204709.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>El atributo <code>b</code> es opcional. Por default, no se devuelve al cliente.</p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"note\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"3d52de3b-a2b4-497e-ae90-d4d7b1000e7c\"><ac:rich-text-body><p>Si bien no se devuelve el atributo <code>b</code>, debido a la implementaci&oacute;n de la feature es necesario que el objeto que se devuelve en la implementaci&oacute;n de la operaci&oacute;n tenga el getter <code>b</code> .</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"b82ff4aa-e52e-447e-b014-25565b427c1b\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb\n\nhandle_operation(:test_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: {\n      a: :a\n    }\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1086\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-204934.png\" ac:width=\"700\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-204934.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Obtenemos un error <code>InvalidGetterError</code> debido a que el objeto devuelto no tiene un getter <code>b</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image></ac:rich-text-body></ac:structured-macro><h1>Ejemplo #1: devolver seg&uacute;n el cliente solicita el par&aacute;metro opcional.</h1><p>Se agrega a la operation:</p><ul><li><p>Un par&aacute;metro en la request para que el cliente pueda indicar qu&eacute; par&aacute;metros opcionales quiere recibir. Es un array de strings</p><p>Este par&aacute;metro puede estar anidado dentro de otro, no necesariamente tiene que estar en el primer nivel. Es responsabilidad del programador el manejo de este par&aacute;metro.</p></li><li><p>Un par&aacute;metro en la response para indicar que la respuesta puede incluir par&aacute;metros opcionales. Esto es necesario para el funcionamiento de la feature. No significa que el json de la respuesta vaya a tener el atributo <code>extra_response_attributes</code> y que su valor va a ser un array de strings. Es solo una limitaci&oacute;n y requisito de la implementaci&oacute;n.</p></li></ul><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"62fd4c3b-f26e-4ac1-8e83-e4bc9410604f\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# operations.yml\n\ntest_optional_attrs:\n  name: probar atrs opcionales\n  description: Probar atrs opcionales\n  path: /test_optional_attrs\n  method: post\n\n  request:\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parametros extra de respuesta.\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string\n\n  response:\n    - element: test_optional_attrs\n      description: Probar atrs opcionales\n      required: false\n      type: optional_attrs_representation\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parámetros extra de respuesta\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>Se agrega al c&oacute;digo de la operaci&oacute;n un nuevo atributo <code>extra_response_attributes</code> en el objeto que retorna, acorde a lo solicitado por el cliente. El valor debe ser un array de stings. Para el ejemplo, el cliente es el que envia el parametro en forma de array de strings.</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"e4c1b3fd-cef3-4eda-a65e-93ec5c385404\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb\n\nhandle_operation(:test_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: {\n      a: :a,\n      b: :b\n    },\n    extra_response_attributes: params[:extra_response_attributes]\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1038\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205359.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205359.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>El cliente solicit&oacute; el par&aacute;metro opcional <code>b</code> y se retorna</p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"note\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"4739ced2-0f84-4bdf-be1e-a280bdab2d23\"><ac:rich-text-body><p>El par&aacute;metro opcional <code>b</code> internamente es identificado como <code>test_optional_attrs.b</code> por su ubicaci&oacute;n en la representation. Cualquier cadena incluida en <code>test_optional_attrs.b</code> hace que se retorne el par&aacute;metro opcional. Ejemplos:</p><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1007\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205451.png\" ac:width=\"700\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205451.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1006\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205502.png\" ac:width=\"700\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205502.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1003\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205509.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205509.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /></ac:rich-text-body></ac:structured-macro><h1>Ejemplo #2: par&aacute;metro opcional no primitivo</h1><p>En este ejemplo se agrega un par&aacute;metro opcional de respuesta que no es de un tipo primitivo, sino que es de un tipo representation</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"7b52bb7b-b806-48b4-ad68-ff166a59e260\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# representations.yml\n\noptional_attrs_representation:\n  - field: a\n    description: A\n    type: string\n    required: true\n  - field: b\n    description: B\n    type: string\n    required: false\n    optional: true\n  - field: c\n    description: C\n    type: nested_optional\n    required: false\n    optional: true\n\nnested_optional:\n  - field: d\n    description: D\n    type: string\n    required: true\n  - field: e\n    description: E\n    type: string\n    required: true]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"bccee999-a12c-4518-8b77-35a52ca077ae\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb \n\nhandle_operation(:test_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: {\n      a: :a,\n      b: :b,\n      c: { d: :d, e: :e }\n    },\n    extra_response_attributes: params[:extra_response_attributes]\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"997\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205608.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205608.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>El cliente solamente solicit&oacute; <code>b</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1102\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205626.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205626.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>El cliente solamente solicit&oacute; <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1128\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205640.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205640.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>El cliente solicit&oacute; <code>b</code> y <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1127\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205653.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205653.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Por lo aclarado arriba, cualquier string incluida en los identificadores de los par&aacute;metros opcionales hacen que &eacute;stos se devuelvan. En el ejemplo se retornan <code>b</code> y <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><h1>Ejemplo #3: par&aacute;metros opcionales en Arrays.</h1><p>Cuando un atributo de respuesta es un array y el tipo de dato de los elementos contiene un par&aacute;metro de respuesta opcional, para cada elemento del array se aplica la l&oacute;gica de los par&aacute;metros opcionales. </p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"e5b83b8d-24b9-425b-afa9-8b76349d952e\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# operations.yml\n\ntest_array_optional_attrs:\n  name: probar atrs opcionales en arrays\n  description: Probar atrs opcionales en arrays\n  path: /test_array_optional_attrs\n  method: post\n\n  request:\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parametros extra de respuesta.\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string\n\n  response:\n    - element: test_optional_attrs\n      description: Probar atrs opcionales\n      required: false\n      elements_type: optional_attrs_representation # ahora es un array\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parámetros extra de respuesta\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"5d889f1b-b4c0-4481-a5c2-497509b5c377\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb\n\nhandle_operation(:test_array_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: [\n      {\n        a: :a,\n        b: :b,\n        c: { d: :d, e: :e }\n      },\n      {\n        a: :A,\n        b: :B,\n        c: { d: :D, e: :E }\n      }\n    ],\n    extra_response_attributes: params[:extra_response_attributes]\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1260\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205858.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205858.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Sin atributos opcionales.</p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1347\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205919.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205919.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Retorna s&oacute;lo <code>b</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1502\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-205939.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-205939.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Retorna s&oacute;lo <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1552\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-210004.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-210004.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Retorna <code>b</code> y <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1566\" ac:original-width=\"2048\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-210023.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-210023.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /><ac:caption><p>Tambi&eacute;n retorna <code>b</code> y <code>c</code></p></ac:caption></ac:image><h1>Ejemplo #4: par&aacute;metros opcionales en la ra&iacute;z</h1><p>Los par&aacute;metros opcionales pueden situarse en cualquier nivel de la respuesta del servicio, incluida la ra&iacute;z.</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"72fe4242-ccdd-4d41-9e3b-e5de3aa7786a\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">yaml</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# operations.yml\n\ntest_optional_attrs:\n  name: probar atrs opcionales\n  description: Probar atrs opcionales\n  path: /test_optional_attrs\n  method: post\n\n  request:\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parametros extra de respuesta.\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string\n\n  response:\n    - element: test_optional_attrs\n      description: Probar atrs opcionales\n      required: false\n      type: optional_attrs_representation\n    - element: root_optional # parametro opcional\n      description: Probar atrs opcionales\n      required: false\n      type: string\n      optional: true\n    - element: extra_response_attributes\n      description: Parámetros extra de respuesta\n      required: false\n      elements_type: string]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:structured-macro ac:name=\"code\" ac:schema-version=\"1\" ac:macro-id=\"6c3d1bba-52bd-44c0-b56e-24a843da3463\"><ac:parameter ac:name=\"language\">ruby</ac:parameter><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[# service.rb\n\nhandle_operation(:test_optional_attrs) do\n  {\n    test_optional_attrs: {\n      a: :a,\n      b: :b,\n      c: { d: :d, e: :e }\n    },\n    root_optional: 'root_optional',\n    extra_response_attributes: params[:extra_response_attributes]\n  }\nend]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1160\" ac:original-width=\"2268\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-211357.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-211357.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1218\" ac:original-width=\"2262\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-211418.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-211418.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1270\" ac:original-width=\"2264\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-211452.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-211452.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><ac:image ac:align=\"center\" ac:layout=\"center\" ac:original-height=\"1420\" ac:original-width=\"2266\" ac:custom-width=\"true\" ac:alt=\"image-20250415-211505.png\" ac:width=\"760\"><ri:attachment ri:filename=\"image-20250415-211505.png\" ri:version-at-save=\"1\" /></ac:image><p /><p />","representation":"storage","embeddedContent":[],"_expandable":{"content":"/rest/api/content/3900669976"}},"_expandable":{"editor":"","atlas_doc_format":"","view":"","export_view":"","styled_view":"","dynamic":"","editor2":"","anonymous_export_view":""}},"extensions":{"position":861175190},"_expandable":{"childTypes":"","container":"/rest/api/space/BAN","schedulePublishInfo":"","metadata":"","operations":"","schedulePublishDate":"","children":"/rest/api/content/3900669976/child","restrictions":"/rest/api/content/3900669976/restriction/byOperation","history":"/rest/api/content/3900669976/history","draftVersion":"","descendants":"/rest/api/content/3900669976/descendant","space":"/rest/api/space/BAN"},"_links":{"editui":"/pages/resumedraft.action?draftId=3900669976","webui":"/spaces/BAN/pages/3900669976/Picasso+Angus+Par+metros+opcionales+de+respuesta","edituiv2":"/spaces/BAN/pages/edit-v2/3900669976","context":"/wiki","self":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/3900669976","tinyui":"/x/GIB-6","collection":"/rest/api/content","base":"https://qubika.atlassian.net/wiki"}}